1
00:00:06,519 --> 00:00:07,379
(Previously)
The hell did you do that for?

2
00:00:07,410 --> 00:00:08,720
You brought all this on us!

3
00:00:09,929 --> 00:00:12,359
If you're going to kill him,
kill me, too.

4
00:00:13,689 --> 00:00:14,699
What the hell are you doing?

5
00:00:15,240 --> 00:00:18,519
I'm going to keep walking until you give me a chance.

6
00:00:20,699 --> 00:00:21,660
Who is he?

7
00:00:21,899 --> 00:00:22,980
He's my ex.

8
00:00:23,250 --> 00:00:24,539
But one day, he's just gone.

9
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:26,629
Won't you just let Ruerat go?

10
00:00:26,660 --> 00:00:29,210
I told you
this would be the last mission.

11
00:00:29,629 --> 00:00:31,629
Do you think we'd get to come back here again?

12
00:00:32,179 --> 00:00:33,759
Once we wrap up the last mission,

13
00:00:33,780 --> 00:00:36,420
we can go anywhere and do anything.

14
00:00:40,820 --> 00:00:42,530
Don't forget to change your bandage regularly.

15
00:00:47,590 --> 00:00:48,659
So we're not\'85

16
00:00:49,329 --> 00:00:50,859
sleeping together tonight?

17
00:00:51,820 --> 00:00:53,070
I can't.

18
00:00:53,094 --> 00:00:54,226
myasiantv.rest

19
00:00:54,250 --> 00:00:55,649
I have to get this job done.

20
00:00:58,359 --> 00:00:59,740
We'll be away for a while,

21
00:01:00,299 --> 00:01:01,500
but I'll see you soon.

22
00:01:02,350 --> 00:01:04,210
There's nothing I can do to change your mind, is there?

23
00:01:11,230 --> 00:01:12,000
Hey.

24
00:01:14,459 --> 00:01:15,879
Call me.

25
00:01:16,900 --> 00:01:18,329
Keep me updated.

26
00:01:20,859 --> 00:01:21,629
Of course.

27
00:01:22,890 --> 00:01:25,400
But let's not stay in contact for a little while,

28
00:01:26,780 --> 00:01:28,230
just to keep everyone safe.

29
00:01:29,310 --> 00:01:30,180
Okay?

30
00:01:39,670 --> 00:01:40,579
We have to go.

31
00:02:15,919 --> 00:02:17,240
Why do I have a feeling

32
00:02:18,810 --> 00:02:20,539
that we won't see them again?

33
00:02:21,680 --> 00:02:23,280
Don't jinx it, dude.

34
00:02:45,020 --> 00:02:46,531
I looked up and found that

35
00:02:46,554 --> 00:02:48,530
Ruerat has bought all the land
around here to build a condo.

36
00:02:53,219 --> 00:02:53,979
Look here.

37
00:02:59,270 --> 00:03:00,599
This is our new identity.

38
00:03:05,500 --> 00:03:06,719
When should we do it?

39
00:03:09,030 --> 00:03:11,050
Ruerat's secretary wants to meet us tomorrow.

40
00:03:12,319 --> 00:03:13,080
Good.

41
00:03:13,949 --> 00:03:15,289
Let's tell Mother.

42
00:03:15,789 --> 00:03:17,789
We'll deal with this and get it over with.

43
00:03:19,689 --> 00:03:21,460
We'll finally get to be with the ones we love.

44
00:04:29,899 --> 00:04:33,399
"The Heart Killers"
(Episode 10)

45
00:04:41,360 --> 00:04:44,250
Here is the sale and purchase agreement.

46
00:04:45,060 --> 00:04:46,800
The price is 80 million baht,

47
00:04:47,420 --> 00:04:48,970
as specified by the landowner.

48
00:04:49,910 --> 00:04:52,000
All you need to do is sign here,

49
00:04:52,029 --> 00:04:54,000
and the land is yours, Mr. Ruerat.

50
00:05:21,029 --> 00:05:22,420
Allow me.

51
00:05:28,139 --> 00:05:32,250
I've been trying to contact
the owner for nearly a year,

52
00:05:32,259 --> 00:05:33,970
but I never got through.

53
00:05:34,290 --> 00:05:37,129
How did you two get to them?

54
00:05:43,120 --> 00:05:46,000
It's our trade secret.

55
00:05:47,779 --> 00:05:50,319
But since you're a very special client,

56
00:05:51,720 --> 00:05:52,899
I'll tell you.

57
00:05:55,410 --> 00:05:56,779
Do you happen to know

58
00:05:59,170 --> 00:06:01,170
Empire Estate and Property

59
00:06:03,220 --> 00:06:05,839
and Punlert Development?

60
00:06:12,569 --> 00:06:13,399
Dad.

61
00:06:13,800 --> 00:06:14,490
Mom.

62
00:06:21,740 --> 00:06:22,810
What do you mean?

63
00:06:28,540 --> 00:06:29,980
We mean to ask\'85

64
00:06:30,009 --> 00:06:31,699
Why did you kill them?

65
00:06:32,519 --> 00:06:33,649
What do you want?

66
00:06:34,800 --> 00:06:35,860
Who sent you?

67
00:06:35,879 --> 00:06:37,180
It doesn't matter who sent us!

68
00:06:37,680 --> 00:06:38,819
Just answer my question.

69
00:06:38,850 --> 00:06:40,279
Why did you kill my parents?

70
00:06:40,300 --> 00:06:41,449
I didn't!

71
00:06:42,569 --> 00:06:43,819
Answer me!

72
00:06:43,850 --> 00:06:45,519
You're Lilly's boys, aren't you?

73
00:06:46,250 --> 00:06:47,180
Aren't you?

74
00:06:47,199 --> 00:06:48,620
Answer my question!

75
00:06:50,269 --> 00:06:52,620
Did you kill them just because
they refused to sell their lands?

76
00:06:53,680 --> 00:06:55,019
I didn't kill them.

77
00:06:55,310 --> 00:06:57,019
This is no excuse.

78
00:06:57,420 --> 00:06:58,620
Listen to me.

79
00:06:58,649 --> 00:06:59,959
There's been a misunderstanding.

80
00:07:05,660 --> 00:07:06,850
Don't lie.

81
00:07:06,860 --> 00:07:07,990
I'm not lying!

82
00:07:09,360 --> 00:07:12,360
The person who killed your parents
was your mother!

83
00:07:12,569 --> 00:07:13,810
What the hell are you saying?

84
00:07:15,370 --> 00:07:18,750
Lilly killed your parents
with her own hands!

85
00:07:21,259 --> 00:07:24,420
You know I'm not above putting
a hole through a liar's skull.

86
00:07:26,079 --> 00:07:26,879
Listen to me.

87
00:07:27,360 --> 00:07:28,300
Hear me out.

88
00:07:31,649 --> 00:07:33,819
Lilly was once a hired gun,

89
00:07:33,839 --> 00:07:35,329
just like you two.

90
00:07:37,329 --> 00:07:40,220
She used to work for me.

91
00:07:41,660 --> 00:07:44,149
I hired her to poison people,

92
00:07:44,180 --> 00:07:45,439
to kill people.

93
00:07:45,470 --> 00:07:48,779
One day, she said she'd quit and start a family.

94
00:07:49,339 --> 00:07:51,970
So I thought she was getting married and having children.

95
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:55,970
But in the end, she just adopted
the children of the people she killed

96
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:57,740
and raised them as hitmen.

97
00:07:57,740 --> 00:07:59,490
All just to get rid of me!

98
00:08:02,519 --> 00:08:03,980
You're lying!

99
00:08:04,550 --> 00:08:06,209
Mother would never do that.

100
00:08:09,720 --> 00:08:11,120
Say what you want,

101
00:08:11,120 --> 00:08:12,514
- but I call that bullshit!
- Bison, stop!

102
00:08:15,259 --> 00:08:15,970
Hold on.

103
00:08:18,199 --> 00:08:19,319
You believe him?

104
00:08:21,300 --> 00:08:22,740
Think about it,

105
00:08:23,199 --> 00:08:25,000
if she wasn't a hitman before,

106
00:08:27,110 --> 00:08:28,800
how'd she know how to train you into one?

107
00:08:31,160 --> 00:08:33,340
You bastards are more dumb than I thought.

108
00:09:01,009 --> 00:09:02,210
Damn it!

109
00:09:02,889 --> 00:09:05,539
So Mother has been using us all along?

110
00:09:07,299 --> 00:09:09,299
What even was real?

111
00:09:11,740 --> 00:09:13,299
You're still calling her \'93Mother\'94?

112
00:09:15,340 --> 00:09:17,299
What about the lives we've wasted?

113
00:09:17,889 --> 00:09:19,769
What about the freedom I long for,

114
00:09:20,169 --> 00:09:22,600
the love I refrain from?

115
00:09:23,840 --> 00:09:25,409
We killed people we didn't even want to kill.

116
00:09:25,429 --> 00:09:27,950
I told you not to indulge her so much!

117
00:09:30,710 --> 00:09:31,720
Crap\'85

118
00:09:32,350 --> 00:09:34,347
Maybe Ruerat was just trying to mess with our heads.

119
00:09:34,360 --> 00:09:36,299
What the hell would he do that for?

120
00:09:37,179 --> 00:09:38,960
He was on death's door.

121
00:09:40,779 --> 00:09:42,480
Nobody would lie at a time like that.

122
00:09:45,200 --> 00:09:46,330
I'm telling you

123
00:09:47,169 --> 00:09:51,740
I'm not letting my parents' murderer
get away with it.

124
00:09:53,779 --> 00:09:54,470
What do you say?

125
00:09:56,029 --> 00:09:57,009
What do you want to do?

126
00:09:58,789 --> 00:10:00,049
Should we kill her?

127
00:10:02,059 --> 00:10:03,679
She taught us to kill bad people.

128
00:10:04,659 --> 00:10:06,840
What she did to us was beyond evil.

129
00:10:09,529 --> 00:10:10,990
Kill her!

130
00:10:11,450 --> 00:10:13,340
Let's kill her, Fadel!

131
00:10:13,360 --> 00:10:14,590
Kill her!

132
00:10:14,610 --> 00:10:15,379
Kill her!

133
00:10:15,399 --> 00:10:16,580
- Kill her!
- Bison!

134
00:10:19,500 --> 00:10:20,840
I know you're angry.

135
00:10:24,230 --> 00:10:25,450
I am, too.

136
00:10:30,049 --> 00:10:30,970
Listen to me.

137
00:10:33,090 --> 00:10:35,970
We need to pull ourselves together
if we want to deal with someone like her.

138
00:10:35,990 --> 00:10:37,250
We need plans.

139
00:10:39,960 --> 00:10:41,559
She raised us.

140
00:10:42,919 --> 00:10:44,529
She knows how we think,

141
00:10:44,970 --> 00:10:46,360
what we would do.

142
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:49,039
That's why\'85

143
00:10:52,120 --> 00:10:53,450
You need to calm down.

144
00:10:58,820 --> 00:11:03,659
It's not in my nature
to let someone who's been using me

145
00:11:06,539 --> 00:11:08,440
continue to live a happy life.

146
00:11:32,139 --> 00:11:33,809
I think he's turned off his phone.

147
00:11:34,139 --> 00:11:35,389
Can you reach your guy?

148
00:11:36,809 --> 00:11:37,970
Same here.

149
00:11:38,320 --> 00:11:40,320
He texted me before he went silent, though.

150
00:11:41,179 --> 00:11:42,210
What did he say?

151
00:11:44,570 --> 00:11:47,299
\'93Let's stay away from each other
for a bit just to be safe.\'94

152
00:11:50,289 --> 00:11:51,730
What's with that?

153
00:11:52,230 --> 00:11:53,980
Do they think we'll just sit here carefree?

154
00:11:54,559 --> 00:11:55,700
We couldn't stop them,

155
00:11:55,720 --> 00:11:57,159
and they refused to let us help.

156
00:11:57,200 --> 00:11:58,860
Do they think they're superheroes or something?

157
00:11:59,730 --> 00:12:00,580
Agreed.

158
00:12:05,240 --> 00:12:08,340
Why don't you
find out what they're up to?

159
00:12:09,210 --> 00:12:09,980
It's worth trying.

160
00:12:11,259 --> 00:12:13,090
I know what they're up to.

161
00:12:13,120 --> 00:12:14,970
The point is he wouldn't listen to me.

162
00:12:14,980 --> 00:12:16,370
Why don't you try and stop Fadel?

163
00:12:16,399 --> 00:12:17,200
See if you can.

164
00:12:19,200 --> 00:12:20,139
You're right.

165
00:12:22,740 --> 00:12:26,399
In the end, all we can do is
wait for them to come back.

166
00:12:50,049 --> 00:12:52,559
I thought you two abandoned me.

167
00:12:54,330 --> 00:12:57,779
We're sorry we've been out of contact.

168
00:12:59,549 --> 00:13:02,460
We felt really bad for messing up last time,

169
00:13:02,480 --> 00:13:04,970
so we just needed some time to recoup.

170
00:13:09,830 --> 00:13:14,639
It was my idea to keeping our distance from you
until we killed Ruerat.

171
00:13:15,039 --> 00:13:16,529
What do you think?

172
00:13:17,450 --> 00:13:18,419
Is it a surprise?

173
00:13:20,330 --> 00:13:21,409
Not at all.

174
00:13:22,740 --> 00:13:25,220
You two never disappoint me.

175
00:13:27,919 --> 00:13:31,080
Well, now that it's mission accomplished,

176
00:13:31,850 --> 00:13:33,190
can we finally quit?

177
00:13:34,460 --> 00:13:35,559
As you wish.

178
00:13:35,909 --> 00:13:38,440
You can do whatever you want.

179
00:13:40,929 --> 00:13:42,259
Thank you, Mother.

180
00:13:43,299 --> 00:13:45,509
If you need us for anything,

181
00:13:45,539 --> 00:13:46,480
just let us know.

182
00:13:47,289 --> 00:13:49,639
You've raised us.

183
00:13:49,659 --> 00:13:51,120
We can never repay you.

184
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:56,899
You don't need to think about that.

185
00:13:57,480 --> 00:14:01,210
Just seeing you two happy
makes me happy.

186
00:14:02,889 --> 00:14:04,529
If you ever need anything,

187
00:14:04,549 --> 00:14:06,370
just let Keen know.

188
00:14:06,389 --> 00:14:07,970
He'll take care of it for you.

189
00:14:29,759 --> 00:14:30,879
Of course.

190
00:14:31,419 --> 00:14:32,440
Thank you.

191
00:14:32,809 --> 00:14:35,980
If you'll please excuse us for now\'85

192
00:14:37,980 --> 00:14:38,809
Goodbye.

193
00:14:54,299 --> 00:14:56,529
They don't know about your mess-up, do they?

194
00:14:57,570 --> 00:14:58,500
I don't think so.

195
00:14:59,769 --> 00:15:00,620
Good.

196
00:15:02,620 --> 00:15:05,200
At least Ruerat is now taken care of.

197
00:15:05,679 --> 00:15:07,240
As for those two,

198
00:15:09,240 --> 00:15:11,960
we'll let someone professional deal with them.

199
00:15:13,759 --> 00:15:14,960
In this industry,

200
00:15:15,559 --> 00:15:17,220
once you're in,

201
00:15:17,590 --> 00:15:19,049
you don't get to walk away easily.

202
00:15:19,740 --> 00:15:21,279
And if you want to quit,

203
00:15:23,059 --> 00:15:24,539
this is the only way out.

204
00:15:56,610 --> 00:15:57,889
If you miss him so much,

205
00:15:57,909 --> 00:15:59,470
why don't you just go and see him?

206
00:16:02,970 --> 00:16:04,500
I can't.

207
00:16:04,529 --> 00:16:05,980
He won't see me.

208
00:16:06,529 --> 00:16:07,980
What's in your way now?

209
00:16:08,419 --> 00:16:10,309
You already got his brother's approval.

210
00:16:10,330 --> 00:16:11,110
So what now?

211
00:16:11,129 --> 00:16:12,230
Do his parents disapprove?

212
00:16:12,259 --> 00:16:13,750
Do you think you'll be shunned by society?

213
00:16:13,779 --> 00:16:15,019
What is it?

214
00:16:15,379 --> 00:16:17,169
Don't make it sound like the plot of a novel.

215
00:16:17,620 --> 00:16:19,539
But what's in my way is even worse than any of those.

216
00:16:20,909 --> 00:16:22,169
If you love him,

217
00:16:22,210 --> 00:16:23,559
you have to fight for him.

218
00:16:24,639 --> 00:16:26,070
Don't let him do it alone.

219
00:16:26,090 --> 00:16:28,070
You gotta push back when he refuses your help.

220
00:16:28,570 --> 00:16:31,460
You gotta show him
that you're on his side.

221
00:16:33,539 --> 00:16:35,090
Romantic, aren't I?

222
00:16:37,809 --> 00:16:39,409
You're quite a casanova, huh?

223
00:16:40,629 --> 00:16:43,039
I only know the theories,
never put any to practice.

224
00:18:17,960 --> 00:18:18,880
Bison.

225
00:18:25,170 --> 00:18:25,980
Bison!

226
00:18:27,980 --> 00:18:28,740
Hey!

227
00:18:32,930 --> 00:18:33,960
Bison.

228
00:18:35,829 --> 00:18:36,720
Bison.

229
00:18:38,369 --> 00:18:39,960
I know you're here.

230
00:18:41,500 --> 00:18:42,640
Bison!

231
00:18:47,779 --> 00:18:48,460
Kant!

232
00:18:53,960 --> 00:18:55,599
Look where you're going!

233
00:18:55,630 --> 00:18:57,369
Don't you know how to use the damn brake, jackass!

234
00:18:57,480 --> 00:18:58,559
That jerk\'85

235
00:19:00,460 --> 00:19:01,039
Hey.

236
00:19:02,730 --> 00:19:03,609
You hurt?

237
00:19:03,890 --> 00:19:04,380
Hey...

238
00:19:25,640 --> 00:19:26,519
Does it hurt?

239
00:19:28,809 --> 00:19:29,940
No, it doesn't.

240
00:19:30,890 --> 00:19:32,650
Nothing hurts more than not seeing you.

241
00:19:36,259 --> 00:19:38,779
I don't want you getting involved with my mess.

242
00:19:39,890 --> 00:19:42,259
Once I tidy up everything on my end,

243
00:19:42,279 --> 00:19:43,240
we can be together.

244
00:19:45,609 --> 00:19:46,569
So?

245
00:19:47,559 --> 00:19:49,210
You're just going to keep living like this?

246
00:19:50,559 --> 00:19:53,000
If you worry about me so much,
why not just keep me on camera?

247
00:19:53,029 --> 00:19:54,539
I'll be under your surveillance all the time.

248
00:20:02,109 --> 00:20:03,500
I don't like uncertainty.

249
00:20:07,130 --> 00:20:08,309
I just want to be sure

250
00:20:09,319 --> 00:20:10,420
that I'll get to be with you.

251
00:20:11,970 --> 00:20:13,970
I can't promise anyone anything with the way I live.

252
00:20:17,650 --> 00:20:18,779
But I'll try.

253
00:20:23,579 --> 00:20:24,480
No, I don't want that.

254
00:20:26,799 --> 00:20:28,259
You think I'll go on living

255
00:20:28,819 --> 00:20:29,849
if you die?

256
00:20:31,759 --> 00:20:33,380
I won't die.

257
00:20:34,690 --> 00:20:35,700
I'm good at what I do.

258
00:20:46,079 --> 00:20:46,940
How about this?

259
00:20:48,099 --> 00:20:49,319
Let me help you.

260
00:20:50,150 --> 00:20:52,049
Let me help you deal with
the person who hurt your parents.

261
00:20:52,069 --> 00:20:53,960
No. It's too dangerous.

262
00:20:54,440 --> 00:20:55,769
You weren't trained to do it like I was.

263
00:20:55,789 --> 00:20:56,720
Train me, then.

264
00:20:57,289 --> 00:20:58,349
Train me to be like you.

265
00:20:58,759 --> 00:21:00,759
It's not easy, you know?

266
00:21:03,359 --> 00:21:04,390
Did you forget

267
00:21:04,710 --> 00:21:07,190
I was a thief and even a narc?

268
00:21:09,109 --> 00:21:10,420
The audacity.

269
00:21:10,930 --> 00:21:12,400
You want another scratch or something?

270
00:21:21,390 --> 00:21:23,500
I'll help you start over with me.

271
00:21:26,660 --> 00:21:28,420
We will take care of each other.

272
00:21:31,319 --> 00:21:32,769
This isn't just an empty promise.

273
00:21:35,539 --> 00:21:36,890
I'll make it happen.

274
00:22:27,240 --> 00:22:27,799
Hey...

275
00:22:29,710 --> 00:22:30,630
Fadel.

276
00:22:31,140 --> 00:22:32,579
You scared me.

277
00:22:34,210 --> 00:22:35,049
I'm sorry.

278
00:22:38,160 --> 00:22:39,970
Didn't you say we needed to stay away for a while?

279
00:22:42,049 --> 00:22:43,220
I can't help thinking about you.

280
00:22:44,799 --> 00:22:45,859
How's your wound?

281
00:22:46,369 --> 00:22:47,339
Does it still hurt?

282
00:22:50,660 --> 00:22:51,599
No.

283
00:22:52,700 --> 00:22:54,170
My heart hurts more.

284
00:22:56,210 --> 00:22:57,329
What are you talking about?

285
00:22:59,440 --> 00:23:00,700
You hurt my feelings.

286
00:23:01,299 --> 00:23:02,759
I thought you trusted me.

287
00:23:04,849 --> 00:23:07,099
You know I know everything,

288
00:23:07,849 --> 00:23:09,920
but still you push me away.

289
00:23:13,559 --> 00:23:14,869
I'm doing this for you.

290
00:23:16,069 --> 00:23:17,500
I don't want you getting caught in the crossfire.

291
00:23:18,759 --> 00:23:21,140
So you'd rather I wonder whether you're dead or alive?

292
00:23:21,839 --> 00:23:23,839
You think that'll make me happy?

293
00:23:25,140 --> 00:23:26,579
It hurts more than getting shot.

294
00:23:28,769 --> 00:23:29,980
You're so dramatic.

295
00:23:30,940 --> 00:23:32,549
You love calling me that.

296
00:23:34,220 --> 00:23:35,980
If you really believe that,

297
00:23:36,000 --> 00:23:37,029
just go.

298
00:23:38,440 --> 00:23:41,160
Go, and don't come back.

299
00:23:44,390 --> 00:23:45,359
Style.

300
00:23:50,920 --> 00:23:52,420
I don't want to lose you.

301
00:23:53,819 --> 00:23:54,779
Neither do I.

302
00:23:57,549 --> 00:24:00,960
That's why you need to let me help you.

303
00:24:24,470 --> 00:24:26,880
Are you sure you want to do this?

304
00:24:28,019 --> 00:24:29,220
Hell yeah.

305
00:24:30,000 --> 00:24:33,119
When I'm in, I'm all in, body and soul.

306
00:24:34,359 --> 00:24:35,819
Don't say that just to be cool.

307
00:24:36,539 --> 00:24:38,069
I'm not saying it to be cool,

308
00:24:38,099 --> 00:24:39,369
I'm saying it to be yours.

309
00:24:42,599 --> 00:24:43,809
I'm in, too.

310
00:24:44,440 --> 00:24:45,670
I mean it.

311
00:24:46,130 --> 00:24:47,640
I was a narc once,

312
00:24:47,960 --> 00:24:49,319
not to mention a car thief.

313
00:24:50,069 --> 00:24:53,339
I think I'm more than qualified for the job.

314
00:24:53,869 --> 00:24:55,369
Now it just sounds like you're bragging.

315
00:24:56,190 --> 00:24:57,900
I'm not bragging.

316
00:24:58,329 --> 00:25:00,210
With two extra pairs of hands,

317
00:25:00,230 --> 00:25:01,680
we'll make your job easier.

318
00:25:02,289 --> 00:25:05,160
You don't have to worry about me.

319
00:25:06,150 --> 00:25:08,210
I'm good enough to make this
dude fall for me, aren't I?

320
00:25:12,220 --> 00:25:13,319
Stop joking.

321
00:25:14,109 --> 00:25:15,970
This is important to the two of us.

322
00:25:18,960 --> 00:25:20,369
I'm not joking.

323
00:25:20,910 --> 00:25:23,519
Your life is as important to me as my own.

324
00:25:30,190 --> 00:25:31,109
How about this?

325
00:25:31,759 --> 00:25:33,220
We split into two teams.

326
00:25:34,569 --> 00:25:36,720
Kant and I will dig up anything we can find on Lilly.

327
00:25:36,740 --> 00:25:38,569
You and Style go after Keen.

328
00:25:39,869 --> 00:25:41,200
We'll share what we find later.

329
00:25:44,579 --> 00:25:45,980
I'll ask again.

330
00:25:48,529 --> 00:25:49,710
It's not too late to back off.

331
00:25:54,160 --> 00:25:55,240
Ain't no way I'm backing off.

332
00:25:55,859 --> 00:25:57,089
Let's get this over with.

333
00:25:57,099 --> 00:25:59,500
You and I will have nothing to fear from now on.

334
00:26:00,480 --> 00:26:02,480
And I just can't stand not being around you anymore.

335
00:26:05,779 --> 00:26:06,670
You ready?

336
00:26:09,069 --> 00:26:10,380
You can count me in as well.

337
00:26:10,970 --> 00:26:12,230
I'm not backing off.

338
00:26:13,730 --> 00:26:15,730
The four of us are in the same boat now.

339
00:26:16,210 --> 00:26:17,460
If you make it, I make it.

340
00:26:18,559 --> 00:26:19,970
If you die, I die.

341
00:26:20,920 --> 00:26:21,980
Let it end here.

342
00:26:23,559 --> 00:26:24,660
Am I right, bud?

343
00:26:28,769 --> 00:26:30,250
Since you're so determined\'85

344
00:26:31,230 --> 00:26:31,970
Let's do it.

345
00:26:41,990 --> 00:26:43,019
Fadel.

346
00:26:43,359 --> 00:26:44,759
Don't be a sore thumb.

347
00:26:44,779 --> 00:26:45,490
Come on.

348
00:26:47,299 --> 00:26:47,910
Hurry up.

349
00:26:54,250 --> 00:26:55,269
Good.

350
00:26:55,650 --> 00:26:57,849
Now I can finally date without fearing for my life.

351
00:26:59,349 --> 00:27:00,180
Let's go!

352
00:27:03,950 --> 00:27:05,450
Why did no one say it with me?

353
00:27:05,750 --> 00:27:06,930
That was on brand of you, really.

354
00:27:39,740 --> 00:27:42,490
It feels kinda weird to have a new work partner.

355
00:27:43,950 --> 00:27:46,119
I never worked with anyone besides Fadel.

356
00:27:47,650 --> 00:27:49,450
When I worked for the cops,

357
00:27:49,470 --> 00:27:50,910
I always worked alone.

358
00:27:53,750 --> 00:27:55,269
I get scared sometimes.

359
00:27:55,970 --> 00:27:57,009
What do you mean?

360
00:27:58,569 --> 00:28:00,519
I get scared no one will help me if I mess up, I guess.

361
00:28:02,519 --> 00:28:04,049
There's no need to worry.

362
00:28:04,059 --> 00:28:05,799
We're not here to kill anyone today.

363
00:28:05,819 --> 00:28:07,400
We're just investigating.

364
00:28:09,299 --> 00:28:10,910
And one more thing,

365
00:28:13,240 --> 00:28:15,079
I have your back now.

366
00:28:19,289 --> 00:28:20,259
Hey.

367
00:28:20,289 --> 00:28:21,089
Stop it.

368
00:28:21,119 --> 00:28:24,410
We can't risk someone seeing us.
(official website: www.kisskh.la www.kisskh.co and www.kisskh.id other than that are fake)

369
00:28:24,869 --> 00:28:27,710
What cabbie makes out with his
boyfriend so openly, right?

370
00:28:30,349 --> 00:28:31,200
Fine.

371
00:28:31,750 --> 00:28:34,890
I won't distract you while we're on the job.

372
00:28:44,359 --> 00:28:47,039
But you look cool in that cabbie uniform.

373
00:28:50,180 --> 00:28:53,700
You know, like a blue collar jobber\'85

374
00:28:56,079 --> 00:28:57,289
It's kinda sexy.

375
00:29:07,730 --> 00:29:09,559
You just said you wouldn't distract me.

376
00:29:14,359 --> 00:29:15,329
Alright.

377
00:29:25,009 --> 00:29:25,549
Hey.

378
00:29:25,890 --> 00:29:26,569
She's here.

379
00:29:40,880 --> 00:29:41,769
Follow her.

380
00:30:13,279 --> 00:30:14,691
Style, what the hell are you doing?

381
00:30:16,390 --> 00:30:17,931
Why don't you just go and sit with him?

382
00:30:18,599 --> 00:30:20,096
You nearly revealed us.

383
00:30:22,759 --> 00:30:25,107
It's not like I've been trained to stalk people, you know?

384
00:30:26,500 --> 00:30:28,724
You were stalking me for weeks, weren't you?

385
00:30:28,741 --> 00:30:29,845
Well, that was me being my persistent self.

386
00:30:30,380 --> 00:30:32,102
What do you know about this guy?

387
00:30:33,519 --> 00:30:35,136
I don't actually know anything.

388
00:30:42,950 --> 00:30:48,461
I only know that we were adopted at the same time.

389
00:30:49,819 --> 00:30:51,497
We worked in field operations.

390
00:30:51,537 --> 00:30:54,451
But Lilly thinks he's more suited for a desk job.

391
00:30:56,319 --> 00:30:57,839
We never really care about him.

392
00:31:05,319 --> 00:31:06,599
I kinda feel sorry for him.

393
00:31:07,131 --> 00:31:08,931
He's eating all alone.

394
00:31:09,297 --> 00:31:10,930
Why do you feel sorry for him?

395
00:31:11,660 --> 00:31:13,525
He was trying to kill us.

396
00:31:13,851 --> 00:31:14,902
This guy...

397
00:31:20,140 --> 00:31:21,805
I need to get back at him.

398
00:31:22,279 --> 00:31:23,336
He hurt me.

399
00:31:24,569 --> 00:31:25,856
What are you gonna do?

400
00:31:25,880 --> 00:31:26,988
Shoot him?

401
00:31:27,960 --> 00:31:29,330
Can you even kill people?

402
00:31:37,329 --> 00:31:38,400
You're right.

403
00:31:39,576 --> 00:31:41,569
I ain't as ruthless as you are.

404
00:31:43,028 --> 00:31:44,508
Move away from there.

405
00:32:16,347 --> 00:32:16,913
Hey.

406
00:32:17,410 --> 00:32:18,673
Who are those women?

407
00:32:24,029 --> 00:32:26,240
I think they're the wives of some senators.

408
00:32:26,259 --> 00:32:28,107
Lilly is probably trying to get close to them

409
00:32:28,701 --> 00:32:30,700
as a way of getting herself into politics.

410
00:32:31,700 --> 00:32:33,582
Using their wives to do her bidding\'85

411
00:32:33,599 --> 00:32:34,400
That's smart.

412
00:32:36,190 --> 00:32:37,988
We need to be smarter.

413
00:32:38,010 --> 00:32:39,737
We need to get close to one of her minions.

414
00:32:44,039 --> 00:32:45,279
My boyfriend's the best.

415
00:32:47,730 --> 00:32:49,176
Hey!

416
00:32:49,188 --> 00:32:50,554
This is no time for that.

417
00:32:50,576 --> 00:32:51,777
We need to work.

418
00:33:02,960 --> 00:33:04,461
Can you help me with something?

419
00:33:05,289 --> 00:33:06,039
What?

420
00:33:06,061 --> 00:33:06,862
Hurry up.

421
00:33:07,200 --> 00:33:08,330
I have work to do.

422
00:33:09,720 --> 00:33:10,662
Here's the thing\'85

423
00:33:15,204 --> 00:33:16,164
What do you say?

424
00:33:18,420 --> 00:33:19,010
Alright.

425
00:33:23,204 --> 00:33:24,325
What are you going to do?

426
00:33:24,781 --> 00:33:26,096
Keep me in the loop.

427
00:33:27,369 --> 00:33:28,720
Don't worry.

428
00:33:29,329 --> 00:33:31,050
I got this covered.

429
00:33:31,809 --> 00:33:33,644
Gonna need to put myself out there a bit, though.

430
00:34:00,009 --> 00:34:01,119
Who is he here to see?

431
00:34:03,559 --> 00:34:05,559
Meeting at a hotel like this\'85

432
00:34:06,009 --> 00:34:07,273
I bet it's his lover.

433
00:34:10,440 --> 00:34:11,960
If they're dating,

434
00:34:12,420 --> 00:34:13,976
why would they meet at a hotel?

435
00:34:15,090 --> 00:34:17,199
If you ask to meet me at a hotel,

436
00:34:18,159 --> 00:34:20,257
I'd definitely assume you're hiding something from me.

437
00:34:22,119 --> 00:34:23,284
Maybe he's hiding from Lilly?

438
00:34:25,737 --> 00:34:27,730
And you said you're not much of a detective.

439
00:34:30,380 --> 00:34:31,650
I learned it from you.

440
00:34:35,199 --> 00:34:36,273
What should we do?

441
00:34:36,900 --> 00:34:38,405
Wait until he comes out?

442
00:34:41,936 --> 00:34:43,204
Can you do that?

443
00:34:43,969 --> 00:34:45,661
If you can't wait, just go home.

444
00:34:47,170 --> 00:34:48,577
Like hell I will.

445
00:34:49,320 --> 00:34:50,811
I said I'd help.

446
00:34:51,289 --> 00:34:52,514
I won't back down.

447
00:35:01,079 --> 00:35:02,119
I have a plan.

448
00:35:04,699 --> 00:35:06,456
We won't have to wait,

449
00:35:07,489 --> 00:35:09,228
and we'll find out who he's with.

450
00:35:15,371 --> 00:35:16,320
What are you going to do?

451
00:35:23,980 --> 00:35:27,981
Thank you for inviting me out for a swing.

452
00:35:28,010 --> 00:35:30,880
All I do is attend charity events and functions,

453
00:35:30,914 --> 00:35:33,079
it gets so boring at times.

454
00:35:33,519 --> 00:35:35,177
It's all my pleasure.

455
00:35:35,190 --> 00:35:40,188
Women our age
must do something invigorating every once in a while.

456
00:35:40,474 --> 00:35:44,291
It must be so boring helping your husband with his work.

457
00:35:44,307 --> 00:35:46,228
You're right to do something fun for a change.

458
00:35:46,244 --> 00:35:47,199
You are so right.

459
00:35:48,769 --> 00:35:53,021
The gentlemen have pretty young caddies on their side.

460
00:35:53,519 --> 00:35:57,501
Don't you think us ladies
deserve handsome caddies, too?

461
00:35:58,960 --> 00:36:00,125
You are so right again.

462
00:36:01,159 --> 00:36:02,119
Hold on a moment.

463
00:36:04,570 --> 00:36:05,748
I'll go talk to them.

464
00:36:05,764 --> 00:36:06,547
Okay.

465
00:36:12,920 --> 00:36:15,610
Where's the other boy?

466
00:36:16,039 --> 00:36:17,987
I picked him especially to take care of the lady.

467
00:36:18,960 --> 00:36:20,097
I don't know, ma'am.

468
00:36:23,510 --> 00:36:25,199
Go and take care of them.

469
00:36:35,467 --> 00:36:36,400
Hello.

470
00:36:38,547 --> 00:36:39,833
I'm here to replace Ton.

471
00:36:40,909 --> 00:36:41,987
Where is Ton?

472
00:36:44,244 --> 00:36:45,980
He's her favorite.

473
00:36:46,489 --> 00:36:47,639
He has a stomach ache.

474
00:36:47,673 --> 00:36:48,942
He asked me to fill in.

475
00:36:52,179 --> 00:36:53,530
I am displeased.

476
00:36:54,210 --> 00:36:56,233
Do you think you can just waltz in without asking me?

477
00:36:59,670 --> 00:37:01,353
I apologize for Ton's sake.

478
00:37:01,929 --> 00:37:04,588
But I am good at my job, ma'am.

479
00:37:14,289 --> 00:37:15,181
No.

480
00:37:15,920 --> 00:37:17,525
I'll find someone else to fill in.

481
00:37:17,541 --> 00:37:18,605
You can go.

482
00:37:51,210 --> 00:37:52,405
Do you need my help, ma'am?

483
00:38:09,170 --> 00:38:09,971
Of course.

484
00:38:12,222 --> 00:38:16,244
Excuse me, please put your weight on this leg.

485
00:38:16,269 --> 00:38:18,856
Put your right leg forward.

486
00:38:41,130 --> 00:38:43,164
Now, keep your eye on your target.

487
00:38:43,929 --> 00:38:45,114
I see.

488
00:38:45,130 --> 00:38:47,753
When you swing, use the strength in your shoulder.

489
00:38:50,125 --> 00:38:51,010
Like that.

490
00:38:53,010 --> 00:38:54,181
Would you like to give it a try, ma'am?

491
00:38:55,260 --> 00:38:56,440
Help me out.

492
00:38:56,467 --> 00:38:57,376
Of course.

493
00:38:57,708 --> 00:38:58,862
Let's try it.

494
00:39:04,297 --> 00:39:05,599
Wow, you're a natural.

495
00:39:06,579 --> 00:39:07,981
Thanks.

496
00:39:08,862 --> 00:39:10,860
What's your name?

497
00:39:13,969 --> 00:39:15,291
My name is Tonkhao.

498
00:39:16,840 --> 00:39:18,101
Tonkhao.

499
00:39:18,960 --> 00:39:20,485
That's a cute name.

500
00:39:22,590 --> 00:39:27,800
Will you be staying with me all day, Tonkhao?

501
00:39:29,489 --> 00:39:31,610
I'd love to, ma'am,

502
00:39:31,929 --> 00:39:33,416
but I don't know if Ms. Lilly...

503
00:39:33,434 --> 00:39:35,724
I asked him to help you.

504
00:39:39,811 --> 00:39:41,376
I see.

505
00:39:42,079 --> 00:39:46,541
I know sweet guys are just your type,

506
00:39:47,239 --> 00:39:48,697
so I hand-picked him just for you.

507
00:39:48,719 --> 00:39:51,440
Oh, you.

508
00:39:52,889 --> 00:39:55,371
You shouldn't say such things right in front of him.

509
00:39:55,769 --> 00:39:57,445
Now you're making me blush.

510
00:39:57,480 --> 00:39:59,987
There's no need to be embarrassed.

511
00:40:00,010 --> 00:40:04,782
Why don't you let him take care of you for the day?

512
00:40:05,369 --> 00:40:06,405
Of course.

513
00:40:08,936 --> 00:40:09,965
Let me hold that for you.

514
00:40:11,369 --> 00:40:12,867
Let's go to the next hole?

515
00:40:14,699 --> 00:40:15,708
I can help you with that.

516
00:40:15,737 --> 00:40:16,702
Of, how kind of you.

517
00:40:16,929 --> 00:40:18,324
Let me help.

518
00:40:49,889 --> 00:40:51,039
Room service.

519
00:40:57,125 --> 00:40:58,827
We didn't order anything.

520
00:40:59,804 --> 00:41:01,800
I was told to deliver it to your room, sir.

521
00:41:03,822 --> 00:41:04,684
Keen.

522
00:41:04,942 --> 00:41:06,061
Did you order room service?

523
00:41:06,416 --> 00:41:07,342
No, I didn't.

524
00:41:09,291 --> 00:41:11,101
I think you've got the wrong room.

525
00:41:13,050 --> 00:41:14,090
I'm sorry.

526
00:41:17,329 --> 00:41:18,507
Hey!

527
00:41:20,059 --> 00:41:21,994
I don't think you've got the wrong room.

528
00:41:23,737 --> 00:41:25,056
What's going on?

529
00:42:01,420 --> 00:42:03,474
I was waiting when you're going to show up.

530
00:42:13,710 --> 00:42:14,942
How was it?

531
00:42:14,971 --> 00:42:16,050
It was really fun.

532
00:42:16,079 --> 00:42:17,320
What do you think of this boy?

533
00:42:17,342 --> 00:42:18,639
He's perfect.

534
00:42:19,760 --> 00:42:21,347
I'll book him for your next round.

535
00:42:24,539 --> 00:42:26,222
Please have some orange juice and fresh fruits, ma'am.

536
00:42:27,969 --> 00:42:28,708
Here.

537
00:42:31,139 --> 00:42:31,994
Thanks.

538
00:42:39,980 --> 00:42:40,914
It's good.

539
00:42:44,739 --> 00:42:48,719
Thank you for such a lovely day, Tonkhao.

540
00:42:50,250 --> 00:42:51,313
Of course.

541
00:42:52,119 --> 00:42:55,565
It's my pleasure to take care of you, ma'am.

542
00:42:56,456 --> 00:42:58,449
Oh, quit it with the \'93ma'am\'94 now.

543
00:42:58,980 --> 00:43:00,771
Just call me by my name.

544
00:43:00,811 --> 00:43:04,565
Try calling me Nuch.

545
00:43:09,753 --> 00:43:11,750
Of course, Nuch.

546
00:43:12,769 --> 00:43:13,960
Attaboy.

547
00:43:15,809 --> 00:43:18,376
I need to use the bathroom.

548
00:43:18,820 --> 00:43:19,800
Of course.

549
00:43:24,960 --> 00:43:27,416
Don't think I approve of you
for sneaking behind my back.

550
00:43:32,880 --> 00:43:33,981
I'm sorry.

551
00:43:34,639 --> 00:43:37,764
I just want to prove to you that I'm good at my job.

552
00:43:39,742 --> 00:43:42,079
You're lucky she likes you.

553
00:43:43,302 --> 00:43:45,300
I'll give you another chance.

554
00:43:46,599 --> 00:43:48,387
What do you want me to do?

555
00:43:48,809 --> 00:43:50,045
Do what you're good at.

556
00:43:50,960 --> 00:43:52,760
Use your pretty face to your advantage,

557
00:43:53,500 --> 00:43:55,251
serving these old ladies.

558
00:43:56,889 --> 00:43:58,268
Her birthday is coming up.

559
00:43:58,307 --> 00:44:02,324
I want some young things like you
to take care of her and her friends.

560
00:44:02,820 --> 00:44:04,114
Can you do that?

561
00:44:05,150 --> 00:44:05,782
Oh.

562
00:44:06,550 --> 00:44:08,217
Do you prefer women or men?

563
00:44:11,579 --> 00:44:12,530
Men.

564
00:44:13,079 --> 00:44:14,467
But I don't mind.

565
00:44:14,480 --> 00:44:15,217
I work in service.

566
00:44:15,228 --> 00:44:17,708
I know it's my job to serve
people of all genders and ages.

567
00:44:18,170 --> 00:44:19,000
Good.

568
00:44:19,610 --> 00:44:22,159
If you're not picky,
you'll make money.

569
00:44:24,610 --> 00:44:27,599
Find me a few more boys like you.

570
00:44:28,059 --> 00:44:29,268
Make sure your friends are handsome.

571
00:44:31,170 --> 00:44:32,519
All my friends are, ma'am.

572
00:44:35,340 --> 00:44:36,427
Excuse me for now.

573
00:44:49,190 --> 00:44:50,302
Put your gun down

574
00:44:50,873 --> 00:44:52,342
and kneel next to your boyfriend.

575
00:45:07,000 --> 00:45:08,125
Let Style go.

576
00:45:09,409 --> 00:45:10,697
This is between you and me.

577
00:45:10,708 --> 00:45:11,650
He has nothing to do with this.

578
00:45:12,909 --> 00:45:14,257
Everyone who is in your life

579
00:45:15,570 --> 00:45:16,907
has something to do with this.

580
00:45:18,460 --> 00:45:19,445
One wrong move,

581
00:45:22,929 --> 00:45:24,427
and I put a hole through his skull.

582
00:45:31,809 --> 00:45:32,981
No need to be scared.

583
00:45:36,260 --> 00:45:37,605
He doesn't have the gut to do that.

584
00:45:38,650 --> 00:45:40,199
You think you're so amazing, huh?

585
00:45:41,639 --> 00:45:43,302
I knew you were following me.

586
00:45:43,969 --> 00:45:46,811
I even had a GPS on your car.

587
00:45:47,730 --> 00:45:49,467
Why did you think I found you back there?

588
00:46:09,994 --> 00:46:11,661
You still suck at this, don't you?

589
00:46:12,679 --> 00:46:13,788
You did all that,

590
00:46:14,539 --> 00:46:15,981
and I'm still alive.

591
00:46:18,320 --> 00:46:19,405
Not this time.

592
00:46:20,460 --> 00:46:21,976
You're in my turf.

593
00:46:23,559 --> 00:46:25,976
Mother will trust me once she sees what I can do.

594
00:46:26,960 --> 00:46:28,313
What is going on?

595
00:46:28,920 --> 00:46:30,291
Who are these people?

596
00:46:31,987 --> 00:46:32,822
I'll tell you

597
00:46:33,510 --> 00:46:34,896
after I deal with them.

598
00:46:37,360 --> 00:46:39,360
You think you'll get to live a normal life?

599
00:46:41,219 --> 00:46:42,724
Even if you pull the trigger now,

600
00:46:44,456 --> 00:46:46,449
you'll still have to sneak about to see your lover.

601
00:46:49,539 --> 00:46:50,873
She doesn't want us to be happy.

602
00:46:53,239 --> 00:46:54,869
She just wants us by her side.

603
00:46:59,300 --> 00:47:00,822
Listen to me.

604
00:47:03,320 --> 00:47:04,376
It was her

605
00:47:05,789 --> 00:47:07,661
who killed our parents.

606
00:47:16,289 --> 00:47:17,101
That's not true.

607
00:47:18,559 --> 00:47:19,942
Mother would never do that.

608
00:47:19,965 --> 00:47:20,902
Keen!

609
00:47:22,349 --> 00:47:23,737
You're not her child.

610
00:47:24,539 --> 00:47:25,981
The only reason she keeps us

611
00:47:26,668 --> 00:47:28,659
is because she wants us as her dogs.

612
00:47:42,673 --> 00:47:43,434
Stop!

613
00:47:51,125 --> 00:47:51,782
Fadel\'85

614
00:47:53,650 --> 00:47:54,804
Don't hurt Nont.

615
00:47:55,590 --> 00:47:57,382
You dare ask me to spare your boyfriend

616
00:47:58,579 --> 00:48:00,257
when you were going to shoot mine?

617
00:48:05,789 --> 00:48:07,971
You said she killed our parents.

618
00:48:10,570 --> 00:48:12,148
I have something to tell you.

619
00:48:15,679 --> 00:48:16,844
What's your ploy now?

620
00:48:18,380 --> 00:48:20,181
Do you remember when you asked to quit

621
00:48:20,947 --> 00:48:22,940
so you could be with your ex-boyfriend?

622
00:48:26,090 --> 00:48:27,188
What are you saying?

623
00:48:29,780 --> 00:48:30,987
He didn't leave you.

624
00:48:33,559 --> 00:48:35,000
Mother put a hit on him

625
00:48:37,699 --> 00:48:39,605
because she wanted you to keep working for her.

626
00:48:47,987 --> 00:48:49,599
Why didn't you tell me earlier?

627
00:48:51,409 --> 00:48:52,960
She asked me not to!

628
00:48:54,730 --> 00:48:55,880
If I refused,

629
00:48:56,619 --> 00:48:57,793
she'd have had me killed, too.

630
00:49:36,889 --> 00:49:38,708
Let's make a deal.

631
00:49:45,177 --> 00:49:46,699
You get me dirt on Lilly,

632
00:49:51,188 --> 00:49:52,699
and I'll spare your boyfriend's life.

633
00:49:57,539 --> 00:49:58,280
Style.

634
00:50:01,889 --> 00:50:03,068
Don't hurt Nont.

635
00:50:11,880 --> 00:50:13,119
That's for you to decide.

636
00:50:15,222 --> 00:50:16,742
Do you love him

637
00:50:19,045 --> 00:50:20,739
more than your Mother?

638
00:50:36,019 --> 00:50:37,753
That's for shooting me!

639
00:50:41,559 --> 00:50:42,382
Nont!

640
00:50:54,702 --> 00:50:56,699
You really know how to charm everyone, huh?

641
00:50:57,164 --> 00:50:58,699
That lady sure fell for you.

642
00:51:02,262 --> 00:51:03,393
Jealous?

643
00:51:08,159 --> 00:51:09,405
Don't worry.

644
00:51:10,449 --> 00:51:11,907
I prefer younger guys.

645
00:51:16,496 --> 00:51:18,960
I think our next job will be easy breezy.

646
00:51:21,068 --> 00:51:22,353
She kinda trusts me now.

647
00:51:24,914 --> 00:51:25,885
Thank you.

648
00:51:28,409 --> 00:51:31,411
But I think Fadel and I got it from here.

649
00:51:33,769 --> 00:51:34,942
No way.

650
00:51:36,130 --> 00:51:37,690
I said I'd help.

651
00:51:37,719 --> 00:51:38,947
I'll stick with you till the end.

652
00:51:40,364 --> 00:51:42,360
We'll get to start over together.

653
00:51:56,869 --> 00:51:58,456
Will you help me with one more thing?

654
00:52:00,079 --> 00:52:00,960
What?

655
00:52:05,670 --> 00:52:06,621
Put this on me?

656
00:52:11,628 --> 00:52:13,619
I thought you threw it in the ocean.

657
00:52:15,902 --> 00:52:16,760
I did.

658
00:52:17,994 --> 00:52:19,994
I picked it up when I was saving your life.

659
00:52:35,320 --> 00:52:37,257
You really can't cut me loose, can you?

660
00:52:37,969 --> 00:52:39,724
You were furious at me,

661
00:52:40,222 --> 00:52:41,719
but still saved my life.

662
00:52:45,981 --> 00:52:48,817
I guess I really know how to charm everyone, like you said,

663
00:52:50,090 --> 00:52:51,125
but especially you.

664
00:52:53,440 --> 00:52:56,400
You let one compliment get to your head, you know that?

665
00:52:57,070 --> 00:52:59,125
Now I wish I left you at the
bottom of the ocean with the necklace.

666
00:53:00,730 --> 00:53:02,291
Like in Titanic?

667
00:53:02,313 --> 00:53:03,297
Have you seen it?

668
00:53:03,313 --> 00:53:04,422
Of course.

669
00:53:04,456 --> 00:53:05,971
I watched it with my Dad.

670
00:53:07,500 --> 00:53:08,496
The hero dies at the end, right?

671
00:53:09,690 --> 00:53:11,114
Yeah, you're right.

672
00:53:11,137 --> 00:53:14,427
But you know, I read somewhere that

673
00:53:15,170 --> 00:53:18,307
Jack could have made it on that wooden door.

674
00:53:18,347 --> 00:53:20,300
There's a whole experiment and everything, you know.

675
00:53:21,480 --> 00:53:23,170
But dude just can't lose face, right?

676
00:53:23,193 --> 00:53:25,170
He sacrifices himself to keep Rose alive.

677
00:53:27,170 --> 00:53:28,530
But I'm no Jack.

678
00:53:29,400 --> 00:53:30,971
I can't lose face, either,

679
00:53:31,699 --> 00:53:33,204
but I will make sure we
both come out of this alive.

680
00:53:37,840 --> 00:53:38,684
What?

681
00:53:38,954 --> 00:53:40,965
\'93I'm the king of the world!\'94

682
00:53:42,130 --> 00:53:43,079
Come on.

683
00:53:44,039 --> 00:53:46,565
\'93I'm the king of the world!\'94

684
00:53:46,940 --> 00:53:48,108
Stop it.

685
00:53:50,297 --> 00:53:51,822
That's the classic scene, right?

686
00:53:51,851 --> 00:53:53,820
I prefer reenacting another scene, though.

687
00:53:54,250 --> 00:53:55,016
Which one?

688
00:53:55,268 --> 00:53:56,268
The one in the car.

689
00:54:03,840 --> 00:54:04,947
Beep-beep!

690
00:54:05,329 --> 00:54:06,599
\'93Where to, mister?\'94

691
00:54:11,139 --> 00:54:12,353
\'93To the stars.\'94

692
00:55:15,347 --> 00:55:16,907
I'm just reenacting the scene, you know?

693
00:55:20,260 --> 00:55:23,994
Did you forget this part?

694
00:55:24,880 --> 00:55:25,971
Hey!

695
00:55:28,800 --> 00:55:30,480
You'll have to wait until we're in an actual car.

696
00:55:33,690 --> 00:55:34,605
Promise?

697
00:56:07,659 --> 00:56:11,565
I've asked Mother about quitting my job

698
00:56:12,519 --> 00:56:13,981
and moving to the South with you.

699
00:56:15,440 --> 00:56:16,422
He didn't leave you.

700
00:56:17,579 --> 00:56:19,016
Mother put a hit on him.

701
00:56:38,090 --> 00:56:39,302
Are you alright?

702
00:56:40,260 --> 00:56:41,748
You can talk to me, you know?

703
00:56:53,739 --> 00:56:54,673
You know what?

704
00:56:57,668 --> 00:56:59,659
I've always blamed myself.

705
00:57:03,800 --> 00:57:05,061
I thought\'85

706
00:57:08,045 --> 00:57:09,422
He left

707
00:57:10,960 --> 00:57:11,862
because of me,

708
00:57:16,389 --> 00:57:17,947
because he was scared of me.

709
00:57:20,079 --> 00:57:21,960
He didn't want a future with me.

710
00:57:25,960 --> 00:57:27,594
That's why I don't want to get close to anyone.

711
00:57:35,851 --> 00:57:37,427
Now that I found out about this,

712
00:57:40,150 --> 00:57:42,782
I finally understood you

713
00:57:45,119 --> 00:57:47,056
and why you were so closed-minded before.

714
00:57:58,659 --> 00:58:00,360
I don't want to have any expectations

715
00:58:02,289 --> 00:58:03,387
just to be disappointed.

716
00:58:10,360 --> 00:58:12,164
I never thought\'85

717
00:58:18,599 --> 00:58:20,164
that he'd be dead because of me.

718
00:58:30,159 --> 00:58:32,467
If only I didn't want to quit my job,

719
00:58:35,427 --> 00:58:37,420
if only I didn't get close to him\'85

720
00:58:43,239 --> 00:58:44,588
He'd still be alive.

721
00:58:51,460 --> 00:58:53,217
It wasn't your fault.

722
00:58:55,376 --> 00:58:57,210
Lilly was the one who had him killed.

723
00:58:58,469 --> 00:59:00,188
It was her fault.

724
00:59:00,199 --> 00:59:01,981
Don't blame yourself.

725
00:59:03,730 --> 00:59:07,565
You had the full right to love
and to want a future with him.

726
00:59:12,289 --> 00:59:13,804
You see now, Style?

727
00:59:18,480 --> 00:59:20,880
The only thing my love will lead you to is death.

728
00:59:27,490 --> 00:59:29,331
Please just leave me.

729
00:59:32,942 --> 00:59:34,217
I won't even get mad at you.

730
00:59:38,840 --> 00:59:40,827
Live the life you deserve.

731
00:59:42,780 --> 00:59:44,610
Don't leave it with me.

732
00:59:46,199 --> 00:59:47,811
Why would you say this?

733
00:59:50,268 --> 00:59:51,719
It hurts my feelings, you know?

734
00:59:55,599 --> 00:59:58,500
I'm not the type to leave
the one I love to save my life.

735
00:59:59,590 --> 01:00:01,387
I'm not selfish like that.

736
01:00:06,101 --> 01:00:09,148
Love is something you fight for together.

737
01:00:10,320 --> 01:00:13,976
Stay by each other's side through every obstacle.

738
01:00:16,349 --> 01:00:17,902
If I was scared,

739
01:00:17,925 --> 01:00:20,971
I'd have run away the day I found out you're a hitman.

740
01:00:23,550 --> 01:00:25,016
But I stay with you

741
01:00:27,010 --> 01:00:28,800
because I love who you are.

742
01:00:32,130 --> 01:00:35,393
I know for sure that you're the one I want.

743
01:00:59,780 --> 01:01:01,181
There's no need to be afraid.

744
01:01:03,610 --> 01:01:05,217
You and I will be fine.

745
01:01:06,405 --> 01:01:08,400
Everything will turn out alright.

746
01:01:11,661 --> 01:01:13,659
Knowing how much you care about me

747
01:01:15,530 --> 01:01:17,530
makes me certain

748
01:01:18,769 --> 01:01:20,210
that I didn't choose the wrong man.

749
01:01:25,387 --> 01:01:27,777
You deserve love just like anyone.

750
01:03:31,769 --> 01:03:33,313
(Next Week)
We're not your children.

751
01:03:33,342 --> 01:03:35,090
You're not my mother!

752
01:03:37,760 --> 01:03:39,760
You two take this car and drive to the border.

753
01:03:40,000 --> 01:03:40,684
Halt!

754
01:03:44,159 --> 01:03:45,753
Can I ask you something, Cap?

755
01:03:47,619 --> 01:03:49,817
Why not just get married?

756
01:03:49,833 --> 01:03:51,125
I'm asking you to marry me.

757
01:03:51,153 --> 01:03:52,297
So will you?

758
01:03:53,068 --> 01:03:54,760
Let's be happy today.

759
01:03:54,782 --> 01:03:57,782
Too bad I didn't see this side of yours from the get-go.

760
01:03:57,827 --> 01:03:59,233
Ever since I met you,

761
01:03:59,559 --> 01:04:01,994
all I want to do is keep living
just so I get to be with you longer.
